getParagraphContent

@Deprecated
public java.util.List<java.lang.Object> getParagraphContent()
Deprecated. 

Gets the value of the paragraphContent property.

This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the paragraphContent property.

For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

    getParagraphContent().add(newItem);
